                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/8–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-11T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 11, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6366. The President has now approved the procedure set forth in last paragraph of
                    Department’s 6318, August 10, 6 p.m., for informing the Chinese of the German
                    surrender terms.</p>
                <p>Please inform your British and Soviet colleagues on the EAC of our desire to
                    proceed in this manner, explaining that it will be done on the direct
                    instructions of the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
